She was born on a spring night when the stars had reached their highest and the moon began to fade. Her screams of life brought with them the dawn and the rise of a new sun, a new season and a new promise to the world. She was of noble birth, though none know of this until this day, for she has never spoken of it. Her father was a gentle man, one who had great love of nature, and of the wilderness, and her mother was a Sorceress and a Lady of ancient noble decent. The love her mother and father shared was not one that was condoned by all, yet they would not allow that to get in their way. <br>
On the birth of the babe, it was decided that she would be brought up away from her parents. Her mother was becoming a powerful diplomat and her father needed to accompany her in her travels. They sent her to Felwithe, the most known of the High Elven cities so that she may grow and be educated as one of her standing should. <br>
And so she aged, the child. She learnt her skills and spells. And by her tenth year it was apparent that she was destined to become an Enchantress.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/utressadragonschild.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tressa Dragonschild</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#B30000>(7/15/02 11:52:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: For when the Dragons came.....</span><hr size=1> Part II- Dragons<br>
She was but Eleven years of age when the Dragons came to Norrath. Powerful beasts of fire and air. Though they were feared by some, they were not feared by the child. When they soared through the skies she watched them, marvelling at their strength, their grace and their beauty. And one day, when the Dragons soared across the sky, she left Felwithe to find them. <br>
She travelled far to the distant continent of Antonica to try to reach the Dragons. And one day she succeeded. They streaked across the sky in their shimmering beauty, reds and golds and whites and greens. She ran to them, calling out to them with their mind and heart. And one listened. A white Dragon heard her calls and descended to her. <br>
She approached the beast, tentative at first, but confident as she did not fear her. And the Dragon spoke to her. Words that passed beyond verbal meaning. And the message was clear...they wanted her, the Dragons. They were lonely. Their race was dying out, less soared across the sky. They wanted a new Child.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=59.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=59.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.emailToFriend?topicID=59.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.threadControl?topicID=59.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=59.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=59.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub70.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:<